Summary
Business Analysts design and document work flow, manage and provide solutions to business unit ideas, trends, and concepts appropriately through the latest technological paths. The analyst understands the customer’s business requirements and process management, and then translates them to software requirements, and helps implement these on established platforms. A Business Analyst is a technical position that also plans, coordinates, implements, and finalizes projects per defined specifications and deadlines, all while keeping the project within budget.
Essential Duties And Responsibilities
Collect and analyze business requirements and translate to appropriate software design;
Assess requirements and provide suggested workflow, software platforms and/or solutions to business needs;
Designs and implement solutions on established platforms;
Maintain and monitor assigned workflows and solutions;
Create and maintain user documentation for provided solutions;
Communicate effectively with internal customers regarding projects, solutions development through delivery of final product to ensure scope and budget requirements are met effectively;
Manage change request process for new and existing solutions;
Develop testing for all new roll out and upgrades from scenario design through test documentation retention;
Other duties as assigned.
Experience And Education
Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience;
Minimum of 4 years’ experience required;
Experience in Microsoft applications with a focus in MS Dynamics and development.
Knowledge Skills And Abilities
Excellent oral and written communication skills;
SQL and VBA preferred;
MS Dynamics preferred;
Visio preferred;
Ability to write and document workflows required.
Language Skills
Requires the ability to record and deliver information, to explain procedures, to follow oral and written instructions. Ability to read, analyze, and interpret a variety of correspondence, reports, forms, articles, proposals, contracts, and common scientific and technical journals. Ability to prepare correspondence, reports, forms, evaluations; and to respond to common inquiries or complaints using prescribed formats and conforming to all rules of punctuation, grammar, diction, and style. Ability to effectively present information to a variety of diverse audiences with poise, voice control, and confidence.
Reasoning Ability
Ability to define problems, collect data, establish facts, and draw valid conclusions. Ability to interpret an extensive variety of technical instructions in mathematical or diagram form and deal with several abstract and concrete variables.
